SIMPLE: entablature
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entablature
<hw>En*tab"la*ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>entablature</ets>: cf. It <ets>intavolatura</ets>, fr. LL.
<ets>intabulare</ets> to construct a basis; L. <ets>in + tabulatum</ets>
board work, flooring, fr. <ets>tabula</ets>. See <er>Table</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The superstructure which lies horizontally upon
the columns. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Column</er>,
<er>Cornice</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It is commonly divided into <part>architrave</part>, the
part immediately above the column; <part>frieze</part>, the central
space; and <part>cornice</part>, the upper projecting moldings.</note>
<rj><au>Parker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entablement</ent>⟦br⟧
